    <div class="container my-5 w-60">
      <p><b>Kiki’s Kwik Mart</b> is a little grocery store in Brighton, MA. It specializes in Irish food and has a wide variety
        of international products. That store is amazing! In Kiki’s you can find really unique products you won’t be able
        to see in traditional supermarkets. It has been serving delicious food to the community for more than three decades,
        but there’s no way to look up the products online.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container pb-2 my-5 w-60 border-style">
      <h3 class="font-weight-bold my-3">Results:</h3>
      <div class="container px-0">
        <p>The e-commerce platform has been added to the local grocery store. Thus, MA residents have got an opportunity
          to have products they like delivered and the business is gaining a significant increase in sales.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!--------------------- Research ------------------->



    <div class="container pt-5 w-60">
      <h2 class="text-center mb-5">Research</h2>
      <p>I started my research conducting a series of <b>interviews.</b> With the use of screener questions I targeted audience that
        were either customers in that particular store or just international food shoppers. My goal was to figure out the shopping
        habits they have and the problems they face. I asked a number of questions starting from “What you don’t like about shopping
        international products?” to “How often do you notice the products on sale?”.</p>
    </div>



    <div class="container w-60 my-5">


    <div class="row align-items-center my-5">

      <div class="col-6 px-0">
        <h3 class="text-center mb-5 font-weight-bold">Problem statement</h3>
        <img src="images/kiki/problem.jpg" class="w-75 mx-auto" alt="">
        <p class="text-center my-3 px-5 font-italic font-weight-bold">For some people knowing the ingredients is life important.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-6 overview">
        <p>The interviews gave me a pretty clear insight that shopping international food can be really problematic!</p>
        <ul>
          <p><li>The stores that are specialized in international food are <b>not as accessible</b> as regular supermarkets. Even if you
            are a huge fan of Irish food but you live far from Brighton, you may not want to spend time to get there.</li></p>

          <li>Most of the <b>products are unfamiliar</b> as they often labeled and <b>described in its origin language.</b> The main pain point
            is that when you buy the product, you <b>don’t know what is it</b>, how is it going to taste or if you can actually eat it.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container border-style my-5 w-60">
      <h3 class="my-3 text-center font-weight-bold">Hypothesis</h3>
      <p>I believe that by adding e-commerce to the website that has an efficient navigation and product description will help international
        food lovers to buy the products they want more easily. I will know this to be true when I see that customers from any part of MA can
        find the products they need and have them delivered from Kiki’s Kwik Mart.</p>
    </div>

    <!---------------------------------- Card sorting  ----------------------------->
    <div class="container ">
      <h3 class="text-center my-5 font-weight-bold">Card sorting </h3>
      <div class="row align-items-center">

        <div class="col">
          <img src="images/kiki/card-sorting.png" class="w-60 my-auto mx-auto modal-image" alt="">
