        </div>
        <div class="col">
          <p>
            In order to build intuitive navigation, I made a list of 100 products from the store and conducted <b>5 open and 3 closed card sorts.</b> The categorization of
            some products got really tricky. There were category names that were just too specific for the wide range of products that Kiki’s offer (e.g. the
            “Cheese” category or “insect repellent”).</p>
          <p>So I <b>united some categories</b> which looked similar and <b>created subcategories</b> for those that stood out. After that I did closed card sorts and tried them
            out making iterations based on user’s feedback after each session.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

