      <div class="container w-60 my-5">
        <h3 class="my-4 font-weight-bold">Usability testing</h3>
        <p>After a round of usability testing, I noticed the tendency that users do not pay attention
          to filters and not use them even if they are challenged to find something very specific. As
          a result, I <b>highlighted the headings</b> making them bold and <b>put the headings closer to checkboxes</b>
           based on the principle of proximity. That little twig helped me to make filters more visible and clearer for the user.</p>
      </div>
