      <div class="container w-60 pb-5 my-5">
        <p class="my-5">The checkout form was initially located on single page with the areas that fold up as the user
          fills out the fields. However, tests have shown that it is confusing, because that way user did not have a chance
          to confirm the action. The solution I found is to <b>break down the form to three pages</b> and use the <b>“Save” buttons.</b>
          I also used the <b>breadcrumb</b> to show how many steps are left. Such iteration helped users easily complete the payment
          and place the order.</p>
